 Gujarat Sales Tax Act, 1969-49(2)-Read with Arts. 301, 303(1) and 304(a)-Imposition of tax must not be such as to discriminate between goods imported from other States and similar goods manufactured within the State-Discrimination cannot be supported by reference to Art. 39(b) and (c)-The proper course to be followed by the Court while striking down such discriminatory measures to give effect to the statutory intention.
 
